                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                       <seg type="script">Twentieth-century script.</seg>
                        <date notBefore="1950" notAfter="1952"/>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <desc>Careful but irregular; by a poorly trained scribe (name:  <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11944GabraM">Gabra Māryām of Māḫbara Sǝllāse</persName>).
                          Written in large (<hi rendition="simple:italic">ca</hi> 1 cm high) letters.
                          The scribe distinguishes the characters ስ and ሰ only in the beginning of the text
                          and further writes both as ሰ. The same hand as <ref type="hand" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/DSEthiop22#h1">Hand 1 of <hi rendition="simple:smallcaps">MS</hi> DS Ethiop. 22</ref>.</desc>
                     </handNote>
